snippet.textDisplay:
Aahhh the old switch-a-roo. This kinda happened to my aunt a few years back. My uncle had this one dog for YEARS. Got another dog so they can mate yet they didn't. My aunt wasn't a dog person and convinced my uncle to adopt this stray kitten that she fed every day. They got his shots etc. Named him Red. Now Red was an evil little ahole. He would always hiss at everyone but my aunt. He hated everyone. Well after a year Red died. My aunt allowed him to go out all the time and one morning before work seen him dead underneath the neighbor's car. Yes we are sure it was gruesome.. Not even a week later we see another cat that looks exactly like Red. Same orange ish red tint so she adopted him too. Named him Red. He was barely in the house too. By then my aunt didn't care as much as she did for the first one. I think she missed him. Anyway Red 2.0 was nicer than the first. Though Red was a she and not too long after got pregnant so my aunt took it to a shelter. She still feeds stray cats. My uncle's dog he had for years (that I loved) was killed by another dog so now they have one dog and strange cats meowing on their front lawn.

Sorry for the long story. The end
